{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":7823,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-14T19:58:33.000Z","cooked":"...\n\u003cp\u003eIs it sizedivisor establish this ratio for this?\u003cbr\u003e\nI mean if I set sizedivisor=‚Äú0.5 0.5‚Äù new RT will be have a twice smaller than current frame size?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:13.565Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":18,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":91.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7824,"name":"","username":"franck22000","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/f/f4b2a3/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-09-14T20:05:10.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003esizedivisor=‚Äú2.0, 2.0‚Äù will work better \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/stuck_out_tongue.png?v=5\" title=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":stuck_out_tongue:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eor you can use sizemultiplier=‚Äú0.5, 0.5‚Äù\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:13.626Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":10,"readers_count":9,"score":2.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":174,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7825,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-14T20:54:53.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003ehi )\u003cbr\u003e\nthanks, I got it.\u003cbr\u003e\nnow I see one object with rendered my custom pass for debug I just copy RT into viewport with helps quad command\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"fog\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"base\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"forwardlights\" pass=\"light\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postopaque\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"refract\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"environment\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"alpha\" vertexlights=\"true\" sort=\"backtofront\" metadata=\"alpha\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postalpha\" sort=\"backtofront\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"glowpass\" output=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"glow\" vs=\"CopyFramebuffer\" ps=\"CopyFramebuffer\" output=\"viewport\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[/code]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003edid you know how to add this my RT as light-overlay for main viewport RT ? I guessing that is also needed use the quad command for this\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eadd.\u003cbr\u003e\nI add blend=‚Äúadd‚Äù option for quad command and now it works as overlay\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"glow\" vs=\"CopyFramebuffer\" ps=\"CopyFramebuffer\" blend=\"add\" output=\"viewport\"\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethis is current glow tech (based of diff.xml)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan class=\"spoiler\"\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\n\u0026lt;technique vs=\"LitSolid\" ps=\"LitSolid\" psdefines=\"DIFFMAP\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"litbase\" psdefines=\"AMBIENT\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"light\" depthtest=\"equal\" depthwrite=\"false\" blend=\"add\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"prepass\" psdefines=\"PREPASS\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"material\" psdefines=\"MATERIAL\" depthtest=\"equal\" depthwrite=\"false\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"deferred\" psdefines=\"DEFERRED\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"depth\" vs=\"Depth\" ps=\"Depth\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"shadow\" vs=\"Shadow\" ps=\"Shadow\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;pass name=\"glowpass\" psdefines=\"GLOW\" vs=\"Glow\" ps=\"Glow\"  /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/technique\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eminimalistic glow shader )\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[spoiler][code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#include\u003c/span\u003e ‚ÄúUniforms.glsl‚Äù\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#include\u003c/span\u003e ‚ÄúSamplers.glsl‚Äù\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#include\u003c/span\u003e ‚ÄúTransform.glsl‚Äù\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003evoid VS()\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\nmat4 modelMatrix = iModelMatrix;\u003cbr\u003e\nvec3 worldPos = GetWorldPos(modelMatrix);\u003cbr\u003e\ngl_Position = GetClipPos(worldPos);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e}\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003evoid PS()\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\nvec4 diffColor = cMatDiffColor;\u003cbr\u003e\ngl_FragColor = diffColor;\u003cbr\u003e\n}\u003cbr\u003e\n[/code][/spoiler]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand that I got after this all\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://savepic.su/6132474.htm\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://savepic.su/6132474m.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"\" height=\"\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nnow I guess need to do some kind of bluring post process for glowRT by x and y.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eany ideas how to do this? \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:13.712Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":10,"readers_count":9,"score":17.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://savepic.su/6132474.htm","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"–ü—Ä–æ—Å–º–æ—Ç—Ä –∏–∑–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è 6132474 | –°–µ—Ä–≤–∏—Å –ø—É–±–ª–∏–∫–∞—Ü–∏–∏ –∏ —Ö—Ä–∞–Ω–µ–Ω–∏—è –∏–∑–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–π : —Ö–æ—Å—Ç–∏–Ω–≥ –∫–∞—Ä—Ç–∏–Ω–æ–∫ : —Ä–∞–∑–º–µ—â–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ñ–æ—Ç–æ–∫ : –º–µ—Å—Ç–æ –¥–ª—è —Ñ–æ—Ç–æ–≥—Ä–∞—Ñ–∏–π : —Ñ–æ—Ç–æ—Ö–æ—Å—Ç–∏–Ω–≥ : Free Image Hosting","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7826,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-14T21:46:01.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003etest this with blurred glow\u003cbr\u003e\n[video]\u003ca href=\"https://youtu.be/4EyelxXuXLA%5B/video%5D\"\u003ehttps://youtu.be/4EyelxXuXLA[/video]\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethis is full RenderPath for ForwardGlow.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[spoiler][code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"blurh\" tag=\"Blur\" sizedivisor=\"2 2\" format=\"rgba\" filter=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"blurv\" tag=\"Blur\" sizedivisor=\"2 2\" format=\"rgba\" filter=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" tag=\"glowRT\" color=\"fog\" depth=\"1.0\" output=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"fog\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"base\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"forwardlights\" pass=\"light\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postopaque\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"refract\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"environment\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"alpha\" vertexlights=\"true\" sort=\"backtofront\" metadata=\"alpha\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postalpha\" sort=\"backtofront\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"glowpass\" output=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurh\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"1.0 0.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"8.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurv\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"0.0 1.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"8.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurh\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurh\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"1.0 0.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"4.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurv\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurv\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"0.0 1.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"4.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurh\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"BlurredGlowToViewport\" vs=\"CopyFramebuffer\" ps=\"CopyFramebuffer\" blend=\"add\" output=\"viewport\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurv\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n[/code][/spoiler]\n\u003cp\u003eDid you also find this strange side effect when glow are disappear on far distances ?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003efew glow materials on one model\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://savepic.su/6141693.htm\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://savepic.su/6141693m.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"\" height=\"\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:13.836Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":8,"readers_count":7,"score":1.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://youtu.be/4EyelxXuXLA%5B/video%5D","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":1},{"url":"http://savepic.su/6141693.htm","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"–ü—Ä–æ—Å–º–æ—Ç—Ä –∏–∑–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è 6141693 | –°–µ—Ä–≤–∏—Å –ø—É–±–ª–∏–∫–∞—Ü–∏–∏ –∏ —Ö—Ä–∞–Ω–µ–Ω–∏—è –∏–∑–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–π : —Ö–æ—Å—Ç–∏–Ω–≥ –∫–∞—Ä—Ç–∏–Ω–æ–∫ : —Ä–∞–∑–º–µ—â–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ñ–æ—Ç–æ–∫ : –º–µ—Å—Ç–æ –¥–ª—è —Ñ–æ—Ç–æ–≥—Ä–∞—Ñ–∏–π : —Ñ–æ—Ç–æ—Ö–æ—Å—Ç–∏–Ω–≥ : Free Image Hosting","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7828,"name":"","username":"rasteron","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/rasteron/{size}/55_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-14T23:43:34.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eFinally! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e I will definitely test this out.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:13.980Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":54,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7831,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-15T06:32:58.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYes, finally) But It has one big problem - glowed objects shine through other solid objects, because this is additive post effect.\u003cbr\u003e\nand to solve this problem probably needed in some way render other solid objects into glowRT as black colored I guess.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs anyone have ideas how to do this ?)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eupdate:\u003cbr\u003e\nI try figure out how they do this glow in this article: \u003ca href=\"http://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/130520/realtime_glow.php?page=2\"\u003egamasutra.com/view/feature/1 ‚Ä¶ php?page=2\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nand now I guessing that need to use alpha channel of diffuse TU (viewport) to store glow mask.\u003cbr\u003e\nif material has glowpass then it write into alpha channel on renderpath executing scenepass =‚Äúglowpass‚Äù\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:14.183Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/130520/realtime_glow.php?page=2","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Gamasutra - Real-Time Glow","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7833,"name":"","username":"George","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/g/71e660/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-09-15T09:55:06.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI think Bananaft know how to do it.\u003cbr\u003e\nSee topic below. You might want to ask him or look at his shader code.\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/zarevo-landscape-experiments/1256/1\"\u003etopic1301.html\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:14.332Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/zarevo-landscape-experiments/1256","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Zarevo: landscape experiments","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":281,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7840,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-15T15:49:17.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI think he use some kind of bloom post effect not glow\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI have a new question:\u003cbr\u003e\nto write into binded MRT I make this fix for ForwardGlow2.xml\u003cbr\u003e\njust bind glowRT as MRT with index 6 = ‚Äúcustom1‚Äù\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    \u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"base\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"base\" \u0026gt;\n        \u0026lt;output index=\"0\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;    \n        \u0026lt;output index=\"6\" name=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand add few lines to LitSolid.glsl (before per-pixel and deferred preprocessor definitions)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e#ifdef GLOW\n    gl_FragData[6] = vec4(vec3(cMatDiffColor.rgb), 1.0);\n#else\n    gl_FragData[6] = vec4(vec3(0.0), 0.0);\n#endif\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand my question: \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003eis this index gl_FragData[6] and output index=‚Äú6‚Äù means the same thing?\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nmy new strategy with rendering is that all objects in scene must write color to glowRT(default black) but only glowed objects write to this RT own color.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand second question: \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-b\"\u003ein what scenepass I can processing all visible objects \u003c/span\u003e?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:07:14.800Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":11,"readers_count":10,"score":2.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":1366,"topic_slug":"solved-how-to-create-int-rt-with-twice-smaller","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":148,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":7842,"name":"","username":"codingmonkey","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/codingmonkey/{size}/119_2.png","created_at":"2015-09-15T20:43:33.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI drop previous render strategy with using MRT, because there are have some issues. (gl_FragData[6] - not worked, I got some results only if I put glowRT in gl_FragData[1] (output index=‚Äú1‚Äù) )\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNow a revert to additive post effect, but with some changes.\u003cbr\u003e\nThe first problem what I found: Why we are not able to attach DepthBuffer from main viewport to custom user RT ?\u003cbr\u003e\nalso I trying use ForwardHWDepth with I guessing works fine in case passing DepthBuffer to other RT. But on my custom pass - depth ‚Äúequal‚Äù  I do not see anything on screen, and only on ‚Äúalways‚Äù it‚Äôs draw something.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo I think if I do not have ability to use DepthBuffer with my RT, why I do not use main viewport for this. But at first I save a frame to new tempRT (only color data).\u003cbr\u003e\nThen I clear only color data in main viewport.\u003cbr\u003e\nThen I render my custom pass into viewport without changing DepthBuffer data, use it only for ‚Äúequal‚Äù test.\u003cbr\u003e\nAfter this I got glowMask in viewport RT (clipped by non-glowed obstacles, other scene objects)\u003cbr\u003e\nAnd then I copy this mask into glowRT and  tempRT back to viewport.\u003cbr\u003e\nIn this case it work without shining though scene solid objects.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDiffGlow.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[spoiler][code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;pass name=\"glowpass\" vs=\"Glow\" ps=\"Glow\" depthtest=\"equal\" depthwrite=\"false\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n[/code][/spoiler]\n\u003cp\u003eForwardGlow.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[spoiler][code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"blurh\" tag=\"Blur\" sizedivisor=\"2 2\" format=\"rgba\" filter=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;rendertarget name=\"blurv\" tag=\"Blur\" sizedivisor=\"2 2\" format=\"rgba\" filter=\"true\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" tag=\"glowRT\" color=\"fog\" depth=\"1.0\" output=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"fog\" depth=\"1.0\" stencil=\"0\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"base\" vertexlights=\"true\" metadata=\"base\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"forwardlights\" pass=\"light\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postopaque\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"refract\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"environment\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"alpha\" vertexlights=\"true\" sort=\"backtofront\" metadata=\"alpha\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"postalpha\" sort=\"backtofront\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"CopyColorToTemp\" vs=\"CopyFramebuffer\" ps=\"CopyFramebuffer\" blend=\"replace\" output=\"tempViewport\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"clear\" color=\"fog\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"scenepass\" pass=\"glowpass\" output=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"CopyViewportGlowToGlowRT\" vs=\"CopyFramebuffer\" ps=\"CopyFramebuffer\" blend=\"replace\" output=\"glowRT\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"viewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"CopyTempColorToViewport\" vs=\"CopyFramebuffer\" ps=\"CopyFramebuffer\" blend=\"replace\" output=\"viewport\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"tempViewport\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurh\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"1.0 0.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"4.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"glowRT\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurv\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"0.0 1.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"4.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurh\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurh\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"1.0 0.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurv\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"Blur\" vs=\"Blur\" ps=\"Blur\" psdefines=\"BLUR3\" output=\"blurv\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurDir\" value=\"0.0 1.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurRadius\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;parameter name=\"BlurSigma\" value=\"2.0\" /\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurh\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\n\n\u0026lt;command type=\"quad\" tag=\"BlurredGlowToViewport\" vs=\"CopyFramebuffer\" ps=\"CopyFramebuffer\" blend=\"add\" output=\"viewport\"\u0026gt;\n    \u0026lt;texture unit=\"diffuse\" name=\"blurv\" /\u0026gt;\n\u0026lt;/command\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n[/code][/spoiler]\n\u003cp\u003eGlow.glsl (for glowpass in material)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[spoiler][code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#include\u003c/span\u003e ‚ÄúUniforms.glsl‚Äù\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#include\u003c/span\u003e ‚ÄúSamplers.glsl‚Äù\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cspan class=\"hashtag\"\u003e#include\u003c/span\u003e ‚ÄúTransform.glsl‚Äù\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003evoid VS()\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\nmat4 modelMatrix = iModelMatrix;\u003cbr\u003e\nvec3 worldPos = GetWorldPos(modelMatrix);\u003cbr\u003e\ngl_Position = GetClipPos(worldPos);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e}\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003evoid PS()\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\nvec4 diffColor = cMatDiffColor;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003egl_FragColor = diffColor;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e}\u003cbr\u003e\n[/code][/spoiler]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003elast screens\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://savepic.su/6151685.htm\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://savepic.su/6151685m.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"\" height=\"\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"http://savepic.su/6138373.htm\" data-bbcode=\"true\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://savepic.su/6138373m.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"\" height=\"\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n[video]\u003ca href=\"https://youtu.be/tRxgS1A1ehg%5B/video%5D\"\u003ehttps://youtu.be/tRxgS1A1ehg[/video]\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eupdate:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDiffUnlitGlow.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[spoiler][code]\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\u0026lt;pass name=\"glowpass\" vs=\"Glow\" ps=\"Glow\" depthtest=\"equal\" depthwrite=\"false\" /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n[/code][/spoiler]\n\u003cp\u003eupdate:\u003cbr\u003e\nLittle optimization for RenderPath. Remove Clear command for glowRT.\u003cbr\u003e\nNow I made two version. with downsampled glowRT and without it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eForwardGlow(with twice downsampled glowRT)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"spoiler\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[pastebin]XtFp8hAV[/pastebin]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003col start=\"2\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eForwardGlow(without glowRT)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"spoiler\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[pastebin]0zPTmVXi[/pastebin]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn my test the first RenderPath is little % faster 315fps(1) Vs 305fps(2)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eadd new tech for using Glow with AlphaMask textures\u003cbr\u003e\nDiffAlphaMaskGlow.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"spoiler\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[pastebin]VciQTPv7[/pastebin]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDiffUnlitAlphaMaskGlow.xml\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"spoiler\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[pastebin]ggmkpBY5[/pastebin]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand update  Glow.glsl shader\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"spoiler\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[pastebin]FEWsvXQT[/pastebin]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\